    "last_activity_date" : 1684378311,
    "last_edit_date" : 1684378311,
    "creation_date" : 1684377991,
    "answer_id" : 76277398,
    "question_id" : 9177525,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is fairly straight forward in Java.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>void print() {\n    Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);\n    char[] stringA = scanner.nextLine().toCharArray();\n    char[] stringB = scanner.nextLine().toCharArray();\n    scanner.close();\n    char A, B;\n    int length = Math.max(stringA.length, stringB.length);\n    for (int index = 0; index &lt; length; index++) {\n        A = index &lt; stringA.length ? stringA[index] : ' ';\n        B = index &lt; stringB.length ? stringB[index] : ' ';\n        System.out.printf(&quot;%s %s%n&quot;, A, B);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
